          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Get or set the speech volume for a speech channel.The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "speechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " parameteris a pointer to a variable of type ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "Fixed",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": ".Volumes are expressed in fixed-point units ranging from 0.0 through1.0. A value of 0.0 corresponds to silence, and a value of 1.0 correspondsto the maximum possible volume. Volume units lie on a scale thatis linear with amplitude or voltage. A doubling of perceived loudnesscorresponds to a doubling of the volume.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "This selector works with both the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "GetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " and ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "code": "SetSpeechInfo",
              "type": "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text": " functions.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
